What is HTML?
HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language
Using HTML, we can create Web Pages
Example: Inspect any website say QAFox.com
Browsers can read these HTML and display the content accordingly
Recommended Editor for Notepad++
Download and install Notepad++
Create a Web Page from Scratch
Basic Structure of HTML Page
<html> </html>
<head></head>
<body></body>
Saving the HTML page
.htm or .html file
Title of the web page
<title></title>
Entering normal text in the body without any tags
Different sizes of Page Headings
<h1> </h1>
<h2> </h2>
<h3> </h3>
<h4> </h4>
<h5> </h5>
<h6> </h6>
<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>APPLE</h1>
	<h2>BANANA</h2>
	<h3>cadbuary</h3>
	<h4>cadbuary</h4>
	<h5>cadbuary</h5>
	<h6>cadbuary</h6>

</body>
</html>


Creating a Paragraph 
<p> </p>
Going to next line
<br/> or <br>
br stands for break
Ruler
<hr/> or <hr>
hr stands for horizontal ruler ---> line
<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE</title>
</head>
<body>
	I'm vijay<br>
	<hr>
	I'm reading html<br>
	<hr>
	I'm software developer
</body>
</html>

Creating Links
<a href="https://www.qafox.com/"> Visit QAFox </a>

<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE</title>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="https://hclo365.sharepoint.com/sites/MYHCLTech">Click here</a>
</body>
</html>


target="_blank"
Creating Images
<img src="path of image" width="100" height="200" alt="alternative text" />
Image inside the same folder of the HTML file
<img src="FreeEbook.png" />
Image inside the child folder of the HTML file folder
<img src="sub/FreeEbook.png" />
Image link
<a> <img /> </a>

<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE</title>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="https://hclo365.sharepoint.com/sites/MYHCLTech" target="_blank" ><img src="download.jpg" width="800" height="500" alt="natureimage"></a>
</body>
</html>

Email link
<a href="mailto:abc@def.com"> Email Here </a>

<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE</title>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="mailto:abc@def.com">Email Me</a>
</body>
</html>

Displaying the preformatted text
<pre> </pre>
Displaying text in bold
<b> </b>
Displaying text in italic
<i> </i>
Underline the text
<u> </u>
Strike off the text
<del> </del>
HTML Web Element
<tagName attributes > Content </tagName>
Empty Elements
<br/>
<hr/>
Comments in HTML
<!-- Single Line or Multi Line Comments Text Here -->
iframes
Used to display a web page within a web page
<iframe src="html URL path" height="300 "  width="650"></iframe>
There are other types of frames, where the pages or page portions from the same website can be displayed as frames
Tables
<table> </table>
<thead> and <tbody> are optional
Order lists
<ol> <li> </li> </ol>
Unordered lists
<ul> <li> </li> </ul>
Nested lists
We can create order lists under unordered lists
We can create unordered lists under order lists
Creating Text Box field
<input type="text">
placeholder attribute
value attribute for preloaded text
readonly attribute - Text cannot be modified 
hidden attribute - Text box field won't be displayed on the page
disabled attribute - Text box field will be in disabled state
Creating Password field
<input type="password">
placeholder attribute
Creating a Button
<input type="Button">
value attribute for label of the button
Creating Radio button
<input type="radio">
<input type="radio"> Car </input>
name attribute for grouping
Creating Checkbox field
<input type="checkbox">
<input type="checkbox"> Green </input>
name attribute for grouping the above check boxes
checked attribute
Creating Submit button
<input type="submit">
<input type="submit" value="Submit">
submit button inside <form> </form> tags and you can see the difference, where the form is getting submitted
Creating Reset button
<input type="reset" value="Reset">
This only works inside the <form> </form> tags
Creating Dropdown field
<select> <option> Option1 </option> </select>
selected attribute
value attribute - If this dropdown is inside a form, the value of the value attribute of the selected option will be submitted to the server
Creating Multi-selection box field
<select multiple> <option> Option1 </option> </select>
Creating a textarea field
<textarea rows="10" cols="20"> </textarea>
Text to be preloaded need to be provided between the above tags
Creating the button a different way
<button> Button Label Text </button>
Writing JavaScript code inside the HMTL
<script> </script> tags can be used to enclose the JavaScript code in HTML
console.log("QAFox.com")
var a=5; var b=4; console.log(a+b);
document.write("QAFox.com")
document.write("<h1> QAFox.com </h1>")
document.write("<p> You can find the easiest Software Testing Tutorials here. </p>")
