id attribute for uniqueness - Practical demonstration of this using JavaScript - View Code Here
name attribute
name attribute is used for specifying the name for an HTML element and it has many purposes
name attribute for grouping - As we have already seen by grouping radio buttons 
name attribute is specified for all the HTML elements inside the form as part of their submission
Example: http://tutorialsninja.com/demo/index.php?route=account/register
name attribute and fieldset
<fieldset> </fieldset> is for grouping related fields in a form
Practical Demonstration - View Code Here
And many more
style attribute (In-line CSS)
<p style="color:green"> The color of this para is green </p>
<p style="font-size:30px"> The size of this text is 30px </p>
<p style="font-family:SimSun"> The font of this text is SimSun </p>
<p style="background-color:yellow"> The background color of this text is yellow </p>
<p style="text-align:center"> This text is a central assigned text </p>
<style> - (Internal CSS)
View Code Here
